item.description:
Noanet Woodlands is a beautiful preserve owned by The Trustees of Reservations. We will climb to the top of the hill and also walk through a beautiful Maple and Oak forest.

***** Description from The Trustees of Reservations website *****
Noanet Woodlands features many miles of shady trails and woods roads for walking, cross-country skiing, snowshoeing, and horseback riding. A hike up Noanet Peak leads to a view of Boston's skyline above the forest canopy. The Reservation is named after a chief of the Natick Indians, who camped, fished, and hunted along Noanet Brook.
